#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Types of processes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:122
msgid "The user process:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:125
msgid "is started from a terminal associated with a user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:125
msgid "accesses resources via requests or daemons"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:127
msgid "The system process (_daemon_):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:132
msgid "is started by the system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:132
msgid ""
"is not associated with any terminal, and is owned by a system user (often "
"`root`)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:132
msgid "is loaded at boot time, resides in memory, and is waiting for a call"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:132
msgid ""
"is usually identified by the letter `d` associated with the process name"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:134
msgid ""
"System processes are therefore called daemons (_**D**isk **A**nd "
"**E**xecution **MON**itor_)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Permissions and rights"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:138
msgid ""
"When a command is executed, the user's credentials are passed to the created "
"process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:140
msgid ""
"By default, the actual `UID` and `GID` (of the process) are therefore "
"identical to the **actual** `UID` and `GID` (the `UID` and `GID` of the user "
"who executed the command)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:142
msgid ""
"When a `SUID` (and/or `SGID`) is set on a command, the actual `UID` (and/or "
"`GID`) becomes that of the owner (and/or owner group) of the command and no "
"longer that of the user or user group that issued the command. Effective and "
"real **UIDs** are therefore **different**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:144
msgid ""
"Each time a file is accessed, the system checks the rights of the process "
"according to its effective identifiers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "Process management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:148
msgid ""
"A process cannot be run indefinitely, as this would be to the detriment of "
"other running processes and would prevent multitasking."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:150
msgid ""
"The total processing time available is therefore divided into small ranges, "
"and each process (with a priority) accesses the processor in a sequenced "
"manner. The process will take several states during its life among the "
"states:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:157
msgid "ready: waiting for the availability of the process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:157
msgid "in execution: accesses the processor"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:157
msgid "suspended: waiting for an I/O (input/output)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:157
msgid "stopped: waiting for a signal from another process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:157
msgid "zombie: request for destruction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:157
msgid "dead: the parent process ends the child process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:159
msgid "The end-of-process sequencing is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:163
msgid "Closing of the open files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:163
msgid "Release of the used memory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:163
msgid "Sending a signal to the parent and child processes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:165
msgid ""
"When a parent process dies, its children are said to be orphans. They are "
"then adopted by the `init` process which will destroy them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "The priority of a process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:169
msgid ""
"The processor works in time sharing with each process occupying a quantity "
"of processor time."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:171
msgid ""
"The processes are classified by priority whose value varies from **-20** "
"(the highest priority) to **+19** (the lowest priority)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:173
msgid "The default priority of a process is **0**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:174
#, no-wrap
msgid "Modes of operation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:177
msgid "Processes can run in two ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:180
msgid ""
"**synchronous**: the user loses access to the shell during command "
"execution. The command prompt reappears at the end of the process execution."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:180
msgid ""
"**asynchronous**: the process is processed in the background. The command "
"prompt is displayed again immediately."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:182
msgid "The constraints of the asynchronous mode:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:186
msgid "the command or script must not wait for keyboard input"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:186
msgid "the command or script must not return any result on the screen"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:186
msgid "quitting the shell ends the process"
msgstr ""

