#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "Process management controls"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "`kill` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:192
msgid "The `kill` command sends a stop signal to a process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "kill [-signal] PID\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:198
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ kill -9 1664\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:209
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Code | Signal    | Description                                            |\n"
"|------|-----------|--------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `2`  | _SIGINT_  | Immediate termination of the process                   |\n"
"| `9`  | _SIGKILL_ | Interrupt the process (<kbd>CTRL</kdb> + <kdb>D</kdb>) |\n"
"| `15` | _SIGTERM_ | Clean termination of the process                       |\n"
"| `18` | _SIGCONT_ | Resume the process                                     |\n"
"| `19` | _SIGSTOP_ | Suspend the process                                    |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:211
msgid ""
"Signals are the means of communication between processes. The `kill` command "
"sends a signal to a process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:213
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:315
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:337
msgid "!!! Tip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The complete list of signals taken into account by the `kill` command is available by typing the command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:219
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ man 7 signal\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:220
#, no-wrap
msgid "`nohup` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:223
msgid ""
"`nohup` allows the launching of a process independently of a connection."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:224
#, no-wrap
msgid "nohup command\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ nohup myprogram.sh 0</dev/null &\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:234
msgid "`nohup` ignores the `SIGHUP` signal sent when a user logs out."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:238
#, no-wrap
msgid "    `nohup` handles standard output and error, but not standard input, hence the redirection of this input to `/dev/null`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:239
#, no-wrap
msgid "[CTRL] + [Z]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:242
#, no-wrap
msgid "By pressing the <kbd>CTRL</kbd> + <kbd>Z</kbd> keys simultaneously, the synchronous process is temporarily suspended. Access to the prompt is restored after displaying the number of the process that has just been suspended.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "`&` instruction"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:246
msgid ""
"The `&` statement executes the command asynchronously (the command is then "
"called _job_) and displays the number of _job_. Access to the prompt is then "
"returned."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:248
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ time ls -lR / > list.ls 2> /dev/null &\n"
"[1] 15430\n"
"$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:255
msgid ""
"The _job_ number is obtained during background processing and is displayed "
"in square brackets, followed by the `PID` number."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "`fg` and `bg` commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:259
msgid "The `fg` command puts the process in the foreground:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:260
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ time ls -lR / > list.ls 2>/dev/null &\n"
"$ fg 1\n"
"time ls -lR / > list.ls 2/dev/null\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:267
msgid "while the command `bg` places it in the background:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:268
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"[CTRL]+[Z]\n"
"^Z\n"
"[1]+ Stopped\n"
"$ bg 1\n"
"[1] 15430\n"
"$\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:278
#, no-wrap
msgid "Whether it was put in the background when it was created with the `&` argument or later with the <kbd>CTRL</kbd> +<kbd>Z</kbd> keys, a process can be brought back to the foreground with the `fg` command and its job number.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:279
#, no-wrap
msgid "`jobs` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:282
msgid ""
"The `jobs` command displays the list of processes running in the background "
"and specifies their job number."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:284
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ jobs\n"
"[1]- Running    sleep 1000\n"
"[2]+ Running    find / > arbo.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:291
msgid "The columns represent:"
