#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:299
#, no-wrap
msgid "`nice` and `renice` commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:302
msgid ""
"The command `nice` allows the execution of a command by specifying its "
"priority."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:303
#, no-wrap
msgid "nice priority command\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:308
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ nice -n+15 find / -name \"file\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:313
msgid ""
"Unlike `root`, a standard user can only reduce the priority of a process. "
"Only values between +0 and +19 will be accepted."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "    This last limitation can be lifted on a per-user or per-group basis by modifying the `/etc/security/limits.conf` file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:319
msgid ""
"The `renice` command allows you to change the priority of a running process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:320
#, no-wrap
msgid "renice priority [-g GID] [-p PID] [-u UID]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:325
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ renice +15 -p 1664\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:333
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option | Description                       |\n"
"|--------|-----------------------------------|\n"
"| `-g`   | `GID` of the process owner group. |\n"
"| `-p`   | `PID` of the process.             |\n"
"| `-u`   | `UID` of the process owner.       |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:335
msgid ""
"The `renice` command acts on processes already running. It is therefore "
"possible to change the priority of a specific process, but also of several "
"processes belonging to a user or a group."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:339
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The `pidof` command, coupled with the `xargs` command (see the Advanced Commands course), allows a new priority to be applied in a single command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:343
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    $ pidof sleep | xargs renice 20\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:344
#, no-wrap
msgid "`top` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:347
msgid ""
"The `top` command displays the processes and their resource consumption."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:348
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ top\n"
"PID  USER PR NI ... %CPU %MEM  TIME+    COMMAND\n"
"2514 root 20 0       15    5.5 0:01.14   top\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:364
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Column   | Description           |\n"
"|-----------|-----------------------|\n"
"| `PID`     | Process identifier.   |\n"
"| `USER`    | Owner user.           |\n"
"| `PR`      | Process priority.     |\n"
"| `NI`      | Nice value.           |\n"
"| `%CPU`    | Processor load.       |\n"
"| `%MEM`    | Memory load.          |\n"
"| `TIME+`   | Processor usage time. |\n"
"| `COMMAND` | Command executed.     |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:366
msgid ""
"The `top` command allows control of the processes in real time and in "
"interactive mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:367
#, no-wrap
msgid "`pgrep` and `pkill` commands"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:370
msgid ""
"The `pgrep` command searches the running processes for a process name and "
"displays the _PID_ matching the selection criteria on the standard output."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:372
msgid ""
"The `pkill` command will send the specified signal (by default _SIGTERM_) to "
"each process."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:373
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"pgrep process\n"
"pkill [-signal] process\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:379
msgid "Examples:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:381
msgid "Get the process number from `sshd`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:382
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ pgrep -u root sshd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:387
msgid "Kill all `tomcat` processes:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/08-process.md:388
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ pkill tomcat\n"
msgstr ""
